And

1358
01:13:48,037 --> 01:13:49,663
- Hi.
- Hi.

1359
01:13:55,127 --> 01:13:56,419
Mary Hatch,

1360
01:13:58,923 --> 01:14:01,716
why in the world
did you ever marry a guy like me?

1361
01:14:03,177 --> 01:14:05,387
To keep from being an old maid.

1362
01:14:05,846 --> 01:14:07,297
You could have
married Sam Wainwright

1363
01:14:07,397 --> 01:14:09,099
and anybody else in town.

1364
01:14:09,475 --> 01:14:12,185
I didn't want
to marry anybody else in town.

1365
01:14:13,229 --> 01:14:15,230
I want my baby to look like you.

1366
01:14:15,398 --> 01:14:17,391
You didn't even have a honeymoon.

1367
01:14:17,491 --> 01:14:18,858
I promised you...

1368
01:14:19,694 --> 01:14:21,987
- Your what?
- My baby.

1369
01:14:24,740 --> 01:14:26,241
Your... Your...

1370
01:14:27,118 --> 01:14:28,827
Mary, you on the nest?

1371
01:14:29,078 --> 01:14:32,998
- George Bailey lassoes stork.
- Lassoes a stork!

1372
01:14:37,003 --> 01:14:40,922
You mean you...
What is it, a boy or a girl?

1373
01:14:44,552 --> 01:14:49,047
Now, you've probably already guessed
that George never leaves Bedford Falls.

1374
01:14:49,147 --> 01:14:52,892
- No!
- Mary had her baby, a boy.

1375
01:14:53,602 --> 01:14:55,687
Then she had another one, a girl.

1376
01:14:55,938 --> 01:14:57,973
Day after day she worked away,

1377
01:14:58,073 --> 01:15:00,984
remaking the old Granville house
into a home.

1378
01:15:01,193 --> 01:15:04,779
Night after night,
George came back late from the office.

1379
01:15:08,492 --> 01:15:10,744
Potter was bearing down hard.

1380
01:15:15,958 --> 01:15:17,584
Then came a war.

1381
01:15:18,377 --> 01:15:21,963
Ma Bailey and Mrs. Hatch
joined the Red Cross and sewed.

1382
01:15:22,423 --> 01:15:26,551
Mary had two more babies
but still found time to run the USO.

1383
01:15:26,761 --> 01:15:30,305
Sam Wainwright made a fortune
in plastic hoods for planes.

1384
