01:15:41,483 --> 01:15:43,984
Gower and Uncle Billy sold war bonds.

1389
01:15:44,360 --> 01:15:48,447
Bert the cop was wounded
in North Africa, got the Silver Star.

1390
01:15:48,990 --> 01:15:52,284
Ernie the taxi driver
parachuted into France.

1391
01:15:52,660 --> 01:15:55,788
Marty helped capture
the Remagen Bridge.

1392
01:15:56,164 --> 01:15:57,239
Harry...

1393
01:15:57,339 --> 01:15:59,666
Harry Bailey topped them all.

1394
01:16:00,001 --> 01:16:03,662
A Navy flier, he shot down 15 planes,

1395
01:16:03,762 --> 01:16:08,092
two of them as they were about
to crash into a transport full of soldiers.

1396
01:16:09,719 --> 01:16:12,096
- Yes, but George.
- George?

1397
01:16:12,347 --> 01:16:14,256
Four-F on account of his ear,

1398
01:16:14,356 --> 01:16:16,850
George fought the battle
of Bedford Falls.

1399
01:16:17,352 --> 01:16:19,678
Now, hold on! Hold on! Hold on now!

1400
01:16:19,778 --> 01:16:21,305
Don't you know there's a war on?

1401
01:16:21,405 --> 01:16:23,190
Air raid warden.

1402
01:16:31,950 --> 01:16:33,400
Paper drives.

1403
01:16:33,500 --> 01:16:34,819
Scrap drives.

1404
01:16:34,919 --> 01:16:36,320
Rubber drives.

1405
01:16:36,420 --> 01:16:41,458
Like everybody else on VE Day,
he wept and prayed.

1406
01:16:43,711 --> 01:16:46,580
On VJ Day, he wept and prayed again.

1407
01:16:46,680 --> 01:16:48,833
Joseph, now show him
what happened today.

1408
01:16:48,933 --> 01:16:49,925
Yes, sir.

1409
01:16:50,677 --> 01:16:53,796
This morning, day before Christmas,
about 10:00 a.m.

1410
01:16:53,896 --> 01:16:55,464
Bedford Falls time...

1411
01:16:55,564 --> 01:16:57,850
Hey, Ernie. Look at that.

1412
01:17:03,356 --> 01:17:04,348
It's gonna snow again.

1413
01:17:04,448 --> 01:17:07,726
What do you mean, it's gonna snow?
Look at the headlines. The President...

1414
01:17:07,826 --> 01:17:10,271
I know, I know, George.
That's marvelous.

1415
01:17:10,371 --> 01:17:11,856
Commander Harry Bailey!

1416
01:17:11,956 --> 01:17:14,483
Mr. Gower, look at this,
the second page.

1417
01:17:14,583 --> 01:17:15,818
Now, look, this is for you.

1418
01:17:15,918 --> 01:17:17,319
- This is for you. That's for you.
- Okay.

1419
01:17:17,419 --> 01:17:19,246
- Right, thanks.
- See you again.

1420
01:17:20,915 --> 01:17:23,041
Be sure you spell the name right.

1421
01:17:34,179 --> 01:17:35,671
Extra! Read all about it!

1422
01:17:35,771 --> 01:17:38,215
George, George! It's Harry now
on long-distance from Washington.

1423
01:17:38,315 --> 01:17:39,841
Harry! What do you know about that!

1424
01:17:39,941 --> 01:17:41,426
He reversed the charges.
It's okay, isn't it?

1425
01:17:41,526 --> 01:17:43,803
Reversed the charges?
Of course it is for a hero.

1426
01:17:43,903 --> 01:17:45,271
Harry!

1427
01:17:45,397 --> 01:17:49,442
You old seven times
a son of a gun. Congratulations.

1428
01:17:49,610 --> 01:17:52,111
How's Mother standing it? She did?

1429
01:17:52,446 --> 01:17:53,688
What do you know?

1430
01:17:53,788 --> 01:17:55,481
Mother had lunch
with the President's wife.

1431
01:17:55,581 --> 01:17:56,649
Wait till Martha hears about this.

1432
